1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:06,339
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:12,220
‪[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:17,934 --> 00:00:23,356
[Ibyang] <i>Why would Miss Bebang bring</i>
<i>my sister in a place full of sexy girls?</i>

4
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:25,191
- <i>My sister Ame isn’t sexy.</i>
- [brazen music playing]

5
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:26,401
- [crowd cheering]
- [Ame shrieks]

6
00:00:26,484 --> 00:00:28,987
- Fight! Fight!
- [crowd cheering]

7
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:31,197
Looks like there’s some shady business
going on inside.

8
00:00:31,281 --> 00:00:33,241
[Mongki] <i>Maybe you want to place a bet.</i>

9
00:00:33,324 --> 00:00:34,659
There are new fighters.

10
00:00:35,285 --> 00:00:36,619
[Red] <i>I want to see.</i>

11
00:00:36,703 --> 00:00:37,829
[Red] <i>Don’t you know me?</i>

12
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:41,249
Bro, sorry. I don’t talk to drivers.

13
00:00:41,791 --> 00:00:43,460
[Red groans]

14
00:00:43,543 --> 00:00:46,004
[Atoy] What’s behind that door?

15
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:47,380
It seems very interesting.

16
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:50,633
There’s a special show happening in there.

17
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:52,635
[Atoy] <i>Oh, have you been inside?</i>
<i>What’s going on there?</i>

18
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:57,724
[Georgia] <i>My client said</i>
<i>it’s very entertaining, yet bloody.</i>

19
00:00:57,807 --> 00:00:59,392
[Karla] <i>Why would they kidnap your sister?</i>

20
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:01,061
<i>You’re not rich.</i>

21
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:02,729
I don’t know either.

22
00:01:02,812 --> 00:01:04,898
[Karla] <i>Maybe a syndicate took her.</i>

23
00:01:04,981 --> 00:01:05,857
[Ame] Brother!

24
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:07,859
[rattling]

25
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:09,652
[Atoy] <i>Ame was here earlier.</i>

26
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:11,821
[Mongi] Why are you here?

27
00:01:11,905 --> 00:01:13,406
Show me how tough you are.

28
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:15,366
[Mongki shouts, grunts]

29
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:20,038
You animal, you’re making
it harder for us.

30
00:01:21,498 --> 00:01:27,212
[energetic club music playing]

31
00:01:27,295 --> 00:01:30,048
[intense music playing]

32
00:01:30,131 --> 00:01:30,965
Stop that!

33
00:01:32,717 --> 00:01:37,055
You know Boss Alpha doesn’t
approve of that inside the bar, right?

34
00:01:37,138 --> 00:01:38,723
You’ll pay a big fine.

35
00:01:41,142 --> 00:01:42,143
Okay.

36
00:01:43,812 --> 00:01:44,813
Take him outside.

37
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:47,148
[Mongki] We’ll handle this, Boss.

38
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:52,904
[thug] Come on.

39
00:02:00,578 --> 00:02:03,456
[sinister music playing]

40
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:22,559
[man] Because someone
tried to escape from you,

41
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,727
all of you get no dinner!

42
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:27,063
Let’s go!

43
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,400
Great.

44
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:31,609
The newcomer, really.

45
00:02:31,693 --> 00:02:33,403
What did you get from your stupidity?!

46
00:02:34,362 --> 00:02:40,160
Now, we’re all not going to eat
because of this idiot!

47
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:44,497
[sinister music continues]

48
00:03:07,061 --> 00:03:11,441
[unsettling music playing]

49
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:13,276
He can’t come back here anymore!

50
00:03:13,359 --> 00:03:14,861
[in English] I want him banned here!

51
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:16,279
[host] Yes, Sir Red.

52
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:18,364
He won’t be able
to come back here ever again.

53
00:03:21,242 --> 00:03:22,493
- [Red] Go on!
- [thug scoffs]

54
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:25,455
Someone tried to escape but was caught.

55
00:03:27,248 --> 00:03:28,207
What?

56
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:29,584
Nothing, sir. Um…

57
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:32,921
Someone tried to escape earlier,
but it’s okay now. We got her.

58
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,720
[somber music playing]

59
00:03:41,262 --> 00:03:42,096
Stand up there.

60
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:43,932
[Ame] Huh?

61
00:03:44,432 --> 00:03:48,061
Are you deaf?!
I don’t want to repeat myself!

62
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:52,482
That’s enough, Tessie!

63
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:54,943
Why, Darryl?

64
00:03:55,026 --> 00:03:57,111
If it's okay with you not to have dinner

65
00:03:57,195 --> 00:04:01,157
after our arduous work, I don't care!

66
00:04:01,241 --> 00:04:03,034
I’m sorry.

67
00:04:03,534 --> 00:04:06,120
I just really needed to go home

68
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:10,792
because a child is waiting for me,
so I tried to escape.

69
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:13,211
I don’t know what happened to her anymore.

70
00:04:13,294 --> 00:04:14,963
I’m really sorry.

71
00:04:15,046 --> 00:04:19,467
I don’t care
who’s waiting for you outside!

72
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:20,760
Don’t you get it?!

73
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:23,096
You can’t get out of here, witch!

74
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:27,767
Put that in your head,
so we don’t get dragged down!

75
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:30,228
- [Ame whimpering]
- I said enough!

76
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:32,438
Leave Ame alone, Tessie!

77
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,941
We’re all in the same boat here!

78
00:04:35,984 --> 00:04:41,489
[somber music playing]

79
00:04:46,869 --> 00:04:52,792
[tense brooding music playing]

80
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:58,047
[Atoy] We walked so far.
You’re just wasting your effort.

81
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:00,675
[Atoy grunts, coughs]

82
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:03,928
[Mongki] Don’t worry.
Your night will soon be shorter.

83
00:05:04,012 --> 00:05:05,013
[Mongki grunting]

84
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:06,764
[thugs shout]

85
00:05:06,848 --> 00:05:07,932
- [thugs shout]
- [Atoy grunts]

86
00:05:09,475 --> 00:05:11,602
‪[thugs grunting, shouting]

87
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:27,702
[exhilarating music playing]

88
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:29,954
[Mongki grunting]

89
00:05:33,624 --> 00:05:34,834
[shouting, grunting, groaning]

90
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:44,761
[grunts]

91
00:05:56,814 --> 00:05:57,815
[gun clatters]

92
00:06:00,902 --> 00:06:04,906
[suave music playing]

93
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,158
[suave music playing]

94
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:37,772
[indistinct speech on TV]

95
00:06:47,406 --> 00:06:49,909
- [sound on TV switches off]
- Brother, I’m still watching.

96
00:06:50,409 --> 00:06:52,120
You’re wasting too much electricity.

97
00:06:52,954 --> 00:06:55,373
- Where’s Ibyang?
- Maybe in the kitchen, Brother.

98
00:06:55,456 --> 00:06:56,707
She was hungry earlier.

99
00:06:57,834 --> 00:06:59,127
All right, Brother.

100
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:00,211
I’ll go ahead.

101
00:07:00,711 --> 00:07:03,339
- Okay.
- You take care of that child.

102
00:07:03,422 --> 00:07:04,298
Take care.

103
00:07:08,052 --> 00:07:09,971
[chiming]

104
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:20,857
[pensive music playing]

105
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:25,945
[water burbling in distance]

106
00:07:26,779 --> 00:07:27,905
Damn!

107
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:30,575
[water burbling]

108
00:07:33,202 --> 00:07:34,328
What happened…

109
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:37,331
Damn!

110
00:07:41,461 --> 00:07:42,712
Ibyang?

111
00:07:43,754 --> 00:07:45,673
[Atoy] What happened here?

112
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:46,924
Ibyang!

113
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:47,842
[Atoy] Hey!

114
00:07:49,093 --> 00:07:49,969
Ibyang!

115
00:07:50,052 --> 00:07:50,887
‪Psst!

116
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:54,307
[Atoy] Son of a thread! What’s happening?

117
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:57,393
Hey! What are you doing?

118
00:07:58,644 --> 00:08:00,480
Wait, wait, wait, I’ll do it, I’ll do it.

119
00:08:02,398 --> 00:08:04,108
Ah! What happened here?

120
00:08:04,192 --> 00:08:07,111
[sobbing] I was just washing the dishes,

121
00:08:07,695 --> 00:08:11,157
- [faucet squeaks]
- then suddenly the faucet burst.

122
00:08:11,699 --> 00:08:12,533
It’s your fault.

123
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:15,912
You keep meddling with things.
This isn’t even your house.

124
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:19,916
That’s why I was washing dishes.

125
00:08:20,416 --> 00:08:24,962
Because I wanted to thank you
for letting me stay here.

126
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:28,591
And for looking for Sister Ame.

127
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:31,719
If this is how you want
to thank me, then don’t!

128
00:08:31,802 --> 00:08:34,805
You’re not helping,
you’re just causing trouble.

129
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:41,812
The dishes in the sink
aren’t even rinsed properly.

130
00:08:42,396 --> 00:08:43,773
All right, all right,
I’ll do it, I’ll do it.

131
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:46,984
[somber music playing]

132
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:48,778
[clatters]

133
00:08:53,407 --> 00:08:55,826
Oh, Sister, why are you still awake?

134
00:08:56,827 --> 00:08:59,372
Well, I’m still awake too.

135
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:00,998
I’m not sleepy yet.

136
00:09:03,417 --> 00:09:04,460
Are you still adjusting to the place?

137
00:09:04,961 --> 00:09:05,878
Not really.

138
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:08,172
You, where did you come from?

139
00:09:08,756 --> 00:09:10,383
From Atoy’s.

140
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,927
They have me watch the shop
whenever he’s not there.

141
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:17,056
How did you become close with Atoy?

142
00:09:20,851 --> 00:09:22,436
When I was little,

143
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:25,064
Mom used to bring me to the shop.

144
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:26,899
She was an assistant there.

145
00:09:27,650 --> 00:09:29,193
Since no one could watch me,

146
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:31,654
I ended up hanging out
at the tailoring shop.

147
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:33,281
What about your father?

148
00:09:34,073 --> 00:09:35,324
Do you have a father?

149
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:38,077
He was a helper, so he
only came home on weekends.

150
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:41,247
And Atoy? How is Atoy? Is he kind?

151
00:09:41,831 --> 00:09:42,707
You like him, don’t you?

152
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:44,667
Huh! Oh?

153
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,585
[upbeat music playing]

154
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:47,086
It’s obvious.

155
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:50,673
- [squeals]
- See? I told you!

156
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:52,425
You really like him!

157
00:09:52,508 --> 00:09:55,803
[inhales] Okay, I’ll ask you straight.

158
00:09:55,886 --> 00:09:59,015
It’s a yes, it’s a no?
It’s a yes. It’s a yes.

159
00:09:59,098 --> 00:10:01,517
I like him. Why, is there
something wrong with that?

160
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:03,102
There’s nothing wrong with that!

161
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:05,646
You’re an adult.
You can do whatever you want!

162
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:08,232
You want to be close to him?

163
00:10:08,316 --> 00:10:10,693
You should apply
as an assistant in his shop.

164
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:12,153
So, I won’t have to watch
over the shop anymore!

165
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,071
Right?

166
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,574
[indistinct shriek]

167
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:17,742
Very good!

168
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:20,119
You’re very smooth, very smart.

169
00:10:20,202 --> 00:10:21,537
Hmm.

170
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:24,790
I don’t have a job yet,
so I need to work, so…

171
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:26,751
[in English] This is it.

172
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:29,295
[playful music playing]

173
00:10:29,378 --> 00:10:30,880
Will Atoy like me?

174
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:33,549
I think, as an assistant,

175
00:10:34,050 --> 00:10:36,218
- of course, yes!
- Ah…

176
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:38,095
As a girlfriend?

177
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,058
Try it. He’s grumpy.

178
00:10:42,141 --> 00:10:42,975
- Just try.
- [chuckles]

179
00:10:43,559 --> 00:10:44,977
[playful music continues]

180
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:47,104
[loud exhale]

181
00:10:47,188 --> 00:10:48,022
‪[music concludes]

182
00:10:57,281 --> 00:10:58,866
Where are you going again?

183
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:01,077
You might slip there!

184
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:12,004
What’s that… What are you doing?

185
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:14,131
Stop that, Ibyang! What’s that?

186
00:11:14,715 --> 00:11:16,384
To make it faster, Master!

187
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:18,386
I feel embarrassed.

188
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:20,846
Where did you get that fabric?

189
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:22,681
Where else would there be fabric?

190
00:11:23,265 --> 00:11:24,475
Let me see, let me see.

191
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:27,478
[funky music playing]

192
00:11:28,062 --> 00:11:29,772
This isn’t a rag!

193
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:32,817
It’s the sleeve of the uniform I’m sewing!

194
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,276
You’re unbelievable!

195
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,695
Oh, I’m sorry.

196
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:39,907
- It looked like a rag.
- Oh my!

197
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:41,492
Can you just stay in the corner?

198
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:44,203
Every time you move, trouble follows.

199
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:52,294
That’s Sister Ame’s bracelet!

200
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:53,379
[pensive music playing]

201
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:55,339
What’s the news, Master?

202
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:57,716
Did you see her?

203
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,261
Why isn’t she with you?

204
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:02,138
‪[bucket scraping]

205
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:05,558
Did you pick that up there?

206
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:07,476
So, it’s true!

207
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,979
Is my sister Ame in Endless Nights?

208
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:11,605
Enough!

209
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:14,358
I’ll handle it. Don’t meddle.

210
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:18,362
I was just asking. Is that meddling?

211
00:12:20,739 --> 00:12:25,286
Of course, I just want to know
the update about Sister Ame.

212
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:27,204
I’m worried.

213
00:12:27,288 --> 00:12:30,374
So, did you see her?

214
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:34,462
[pensive music continues]

215
00:12:36,922 --> 00:12:38,424
Hello?

216
00:12:38,507 --> 00:12:39,884
Am I a person,

217
00:12:40,551 --> 00:12:43,804
a plant, air? Ignored on earth!

218
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:48,934
[somber music playing]

219
00:12:57,485 --> 00:12:59,778
Do you know how to use a machine?

220
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:01,489
Ah, machine?

221
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:03,073
[in English] Sewing machine.

222
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:06,827
Oh, I only sew by hand, Miss Cita.

223
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:09,788
But I can learn it, promise.

224
00:13:09,872 --> 00:13:11,248
[feel-good music playing]

225
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:14,710
Ah… Do you know
the different kinds of fabric?

226
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:16,837
Not really. Oh!

227
00:13:18,672 --> 00:13:22,885
Miss Cita, I know I don’t know much yet.

228
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:26,388
But promise, I can learn everything

229
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:27,932
for my Mr. Right!

230
00:13:28,015 --> 00:13:29,266
For TDH!

231
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:32,186
- You’re accepted.
- [chuckles]

232
00:13:32,269 --> 00:13:34,980
Thank you, Miss Cita!
Promise you won’t regret it.

233
00:13:35,064 --> 00:13:37,191
All right, all right. I’ll count on that.

234
00:13:37,274 --> 00:13:38,400
[softly] Thank you!

235
00:13:39,443 --> 00:13:40,319
Oh.

236
00:13:40,903 --> 00:13:43,364
[melancholic music playing]

237
00:13:43,447 --> 00:13:45,449
Oh? Why does this baby look sad?

238
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:46,742
[Tonet] Ibyang?

239
00:13:47,243 --> 00:13:49,161
You look like you haven’t paid your debt.

240
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:51,747
She was scolded by Atoy last night.

241
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:56,085
[Tonet] Oh. Poor baby.

242
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:59,922
You know, it’s okay. He’s really grumpy,

243
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:02,049
but that will go away
once he falls in love with me.

244
00:14:02,132 --> 00:14:03,592
[Cita chuckles]

245
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:06,637
Why are you still sad?

246
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:08,389
What do you want to do?

247
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:13,185
Nothing. I’ll probably get scolded again
by that Grumpy Master.

248
00:14:13,269 --> 00:14:16,272
Just focus on how you’ll be happy.

249
00:14:17,314 --> 00:14:20,276
You know, you look like Catriona Gray.

250
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:23,696
Do you want to be
Little Miss Catriona Gray?

251
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,949
Miss Universe?

252
00:14:27,032 --> 00:14:28,450
Yes, I’ll take care of you!

253
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:31,579
I also want to be Miss Universe!

254
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:32,955
- [Cita gasps]
- [Tonet chuckles]

255
00:14:33,038 --> 00:14:34,456
See?

256
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:35,708
No problem. I got you!

257
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:37,960
[feel-good music playing]

258
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:41,881
If Brother Atoy gets mad,

259
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,048
you’ll cover for me, huh?

260
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:45,926
[exclaims] Yes! I got this.
He won’t get mad.

261
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:47,511
Promise. [indistinct speech]

262
00:14:47,595 --> 00:14:48,596
Oh!

263
00:14:48,679 --> 00:14:50,681
Are you excited? [shrieks]

264
00:14:52,641 --> 00:14:55,185
Here. When I say
three, two, one, walk, okay?

265
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:56,854
[in English] In three, two, one, go!

266
00:14:56,937 --> 00:14:58,564
Oh, three, two… Oh, oh…

267
00:14:58,647 --> 00:15:00,816
All right. Oh…

268
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:01,775
One more! Oh!

269
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:03,611
[Tonet exclaims]

270
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:05,988
Hey! She even spun around!

271
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:07,072
[chuckles] Oh!

272
00:15:07,156 --> 00:15:10,242
This baby is really amazing!

273
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:12,786
You’re better, Sister Tonet!

274
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:15,372
You’re great at applying makeup!

275
00:15:15,456 --> 00:15:16,290
[Tonet chuckles] Oh!

276
00:15:16,373 --> 00:15:19,752
One more. Say, "Philippines!"

277
00:15:19,835 --> 00:15:20,753
- Here.
- Okay.

278
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:21,962
Three, two, one!

279
00:15:22,546 --> 00:15:24,840
- Philippines!
- Very good!

280
00:15:24,924 --> 00:15:27,426
OPEN
PLEASE COME IN!

281
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:29,637
Son of a thread!

282
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,597
[upbeat music playing]

283
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:33,933
What are you doing here again, huh?

284
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,687
This is a tailoring shop.

285
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,774
Not a parlor. What are you doing?

286
00:15:44,234 --> 00:15:45,402
Gosh, Ibyang!

287
00:15:45,486 --> 00:15:47,321
Every time I come home,

288
00:15:47,404 --> 00:15:49,782
it’s either chaos or noise. Noise, chaos.

289
00:15:50,366 --> 00:15:55,496
[mischievous music playing]

290
00:15:57,873 --> 00:16:00,709
- [music concludes]
- Ibyang, ever since you got here,

291
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:03,128
I haven’t had any peace.

292
00:16:03,212 --> 00:16:04,588
- It’s always chaos.
- [brazen music playing]

293
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:06,757
Well, if you want silence,

294
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:09,051
then just hang out in the cemetery.

295
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:09,969
[Tonet mumbles]

296
00:16:10,052 --> 00:16:12,846
Ah, so you’re even being sarcastic, huh?

297
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:15,099
[mischievous music playing]

298
00:16:15,182 --> 00:16:17,518
[chuckles] Atoy, sorry.

299
00:16:17,601 --> 00:16:20,980
It was me. I told her
we should do a fashion show.

300
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:23,983
Because doesn’t she
look like Catriona Gray? [chuckles]

301
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:25,192
- She looks like her.
- [titters]

302
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:26,694
- [Atoy] Catriona Gray?
- Doesn’t she?

303
00:16:26,777 --> 00:16:29,405
[Ibyang] I’m sure
he doesn’t even know her!

304
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:30,322
[clicks tongue, inhales]

305
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:32,866
Exactly. Since she looks
like Catriona Gray,

306
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:35,744
I thought of putting makeup on her.

307
00:16:36,704 --> 00:16:41,208
We wouldn’t have done this
if we knew you had clients coming.

308
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:43,502
Because Miss Cita said

309
00:16:43,585 --> 00:16:46,547
after she leaves,
we should close the shop.

310
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:50,384
Ah, so you’re the one behind this. Wait.

311
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:54,263
What are you doing here again?

312
00:16:54,346 --> 00:16:55,806
Why are you here again?

313
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:57,224
[chuckles] Oh, right!

314
00:16:57,307 --> 00:17:02,062
I’m your newest
and most beautiful shop assistant.

315
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:03,439
[Atoy scoffs] Oh, you?

316
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:06,191
- [Tonet] Yes!
- [in English] Wow, shop assistant.

317
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:08,193
- [in English] Yes.
- And this is the first thing you did

318
00:17:08,277 --> 00:17:10,154
on your first day as shop assistant?

319
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:13,782
Wow! So, who accepted you?
Who interviewed you?

320
00:17:13,866 --> 00:17:15,117
Miss Cita!

321
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,618
[Atoy] Ah, Miss Cita?

322
00:17:16,702 --> 00:17:19,121
- Did you pass her interview?
- I passed with flying colors.

323
00:17:19,204 --> 00:17:21,206
- Well, with me, you didn’t.
- Huh?

324
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:22,624
- [music ends]
- You failed.

325
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:28,380
[somber music playing]

326
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:30,758
Uh…

327
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:31,925
[in English] Sorry.

328
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:34,303
I’m sorry again, Atoy.

329
00:17:36,013 --> 00:17:36,930
[inhales]

330
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:38,891
I’ll go ahead, Bebe.

331
00:17:38,974 --> 00:17:40,726
Sister will leave first. [chuckles]

332
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:42,478
Sorry, Sister Tonet.

333
00:17:42,561 --> 00:17:43,437
[in English] Sorry.

334
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:56,408
Sister Tonet only did this
to make me happy.

335
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:59,453
It’s just that I always
mess up in your eyes.

336
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:03,832
And when I ask about Sister Ame,

337
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:05,459
you don’t answer me.

338
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:11,590
Because you’re so stubborn!
I already told you that I’ll handle it.

339
00:18:12,091 --> 00:18:14,802
Still, you keep asking.
It’s like you don’t trust me.

340
00:18:14,885 --> 00:18:17,554
If you want, you can find someone else
to look for her and help you!

341
00:18:18,347 --> 00:18:19,723
[Cita] Atoy?

342
00:18:19,807 --> 00:18:22,017
- Yes?
- What’s this again?

343
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:23,852
That’s enough!

344
00:18:25,896 --> 00:18:29,983
[somber music continues]

345
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:37,407
‪[music concludes]

346
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:38,367
Darryl,

347
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:42,621
why don’t we all help each other here?

348
00:18:43,372 --> 00:18:46,416
Didn’t you say we’re all in the same boat?

349
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:51,505
Why don’t we all work together so we can
escape and report them to the police?

350
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:54,633
Ame, that’s enough.

351
00:18:54,716 --> 00:18:57,469
Tessie bullying you is wrong.

352
00:18:58,053 --> 00:18:59,179
Haven’t you learned your lesson?

353
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:00,764
What do you mean?

354
00:19:01,390 --> 00:19:03,350
That all of you have lost hope?

355
00:19:04,143 --> 00:19:05,978
[Darryl] They’ve tried that before.

356
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:08,021
Nothing happened.

357
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:12,776
The syndicate that holds us here
has deep connections, Ame.

358
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:15,362
How did you end up here?

359
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:17,656
They kidnapped me.

360
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:21,952
Me, I really looked for this.

361
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:27,958
I heard there was money
to be made for people like us.

362
00:19:28,959 --> 00:19:29,918
Why?

363
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:32,629
Because I need money.

364
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:33,547
[somber music playing]

365
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:37,676
Otherwise, I can’t pay
for my father’s hospital bills.

366
00:19:38,635 --> 00:19:41,013
I signed a contract for ten wins.

367
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,348
I flaunted my skills here.

368
00:19:44,057 --> 00:19:46,685
Not once did I try to escape.

369
00:19:47,644 --> 00:19:49,146
That’s why they trust me.

370
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:54,776
After my tenth win, they’ll release me.

371
00:19:55,652 --> 00:19:57,696
Last night’s win was your…?

372
00:19:57,779 --> 00:19:59,198
Ninth.

373
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:04,369
Do you really believe
that after your tenth win,

374
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:06,622
they’ll release you?

375
00:20:06,705 --> 00:20:08,081
Why not?

376
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:10,792
You’d probably report them to the police.

377
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:12,669
Of course, they’ll make sure you don’t,

378
00:20:12,753 --> 00:20:13,962
especially since they know
this is illegal!

379
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:15,839
I won’t do that.

380
00:20:17,007 --> 00:20:19,384
Honestly, I might even come back here

381
00:20:19,968 --> 00:20:22,137
after paying for my father’s
hospital bills.

382
00:20:23,305 --> 00:20:24,806
Are you serious?

383
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:27,601
You know, I understand you.

384
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:30,604
But this job…

385
00:20:31,104 --> 00:20:32,564
It could kill us!

386
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:35,108
It’s better than having no job, right?

387
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:38,862
There’s no job waiting outside, Ame.

388
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:40,739
Especially for people like us.

389
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:43,075
So, if I were you,

390
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:46,036
instead of fighting this situation,

391
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:47,913
embrace it.

392
00:20:48,538 --> 00:20:50,123
Accept it, even if you don’t want to.

393
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:56,505
We’re different.

394
00:20:57,089 --> 00:20:58,840
I didn’t choose this.

395
00:21:00,217 --> 00:21:03,679
[somber music playing]

396
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,180
[Ame] Brother!

397
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:06,723
I hope…

398
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:07,975
I hope Brother comes back.

399
00:21:08,058 --> 00:21:09,643
[sobs]

400
00:21:09,726 --> 00:21:12,771
Maybe he can help me get out of here.

401
00:21:33,792 --> 00:21:35,752
[phone ringing]

402
00:21:38,213 --> 00:21:40,173
Aren’t you going to answer that?

403
00:21:40,882 --> 00:21:45,095
How could I, when I don’t have
anything to say to him.

404
00:21:45,178 --> 00:21:46,013
[somber music playing]

405
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:47,931
That’s my problem.

406
00:21:48,807 --> 00:21:51,601
I can’t even do my real job

407
00:21:51,685 --> 00:21:53,937
because of what Ibyang keeps making me do.

408
00:21:54,021 --> 00:21:55,314
And she’s so persistent.

409
00:21:57,524 --> 00:22:01,278
So, what happened
with your search for Ibyang’s sister?

410
00:22:01,862 --> 00:22:04,406
I’m still thinking
how I can re-enter Endless Nights,

411
00:22:04,489 --> 00:22:05,949
since I’m wanted there.

412
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:09,995
So, for now, I’ll probably just do
what I was really tasked to do.

413
00:22:10,078 --> 00:22:11,705
I’ll look for Mercardo’s rooster.

414
00:22:11,788 --> 00:22:12,664
‪Hmm…

415
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:17,336
- [Cita] Hmm.
- How are you, Big Bro?

416
00:22:19,129 --> 00:22:21,506
Mom, I’ll get my allowance.

417
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:22,841
[in English] Allowance?

418
00:22:23,925 --> 00:22:27,387
Karla, take Ibyang out.

419
00:22:27,471 --> 00:22:30,432
Bring her outside, wherever you want.

420
00:22:30,515 --> 00:22:32,350
She’s too restless here, too noisy.

421
00:22:32,934 --> 00:22:35,395
- [Karla] Big Brother, I have plans.
- [Cita] Come on.

422
00:22:35,479 --> 00:22:38,106
Please help your brother Atoy. Oh.

423
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:39,775
Make it last, okay?

424
00:22:39,858 --> 00:22:42,027
- Thanks, Mom.
- [Cita] Mmm…

425
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:43,070
Ibyang!

426
00:22:43,153 --> 00:22:44,279
Oh.

427
00:22:44,988 --> 00:22:47,866
[bright music playing]

428
00:22:47,949 --> 00:22:50,202
[Karla] Come on. I was told to get you.

429
00:22:50,786 --> 00:22:53,038
We’re going out. Thanks, Mom!

430
00:22:53,121 --> 00:22:55,082
- [Cita] All right, take care.
- Psst! Banana cue.

431
00:22:57,334 --> 00:22:59,878
[phone ringing]

432
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:09,930
- [upbeat music playing]
- [boy 1 exclaiming] Oh…

433
00:23:10,013 --> 00:23:11,306
[boy 2] Come on!

434
00:23:11,389 --> 00:23:13,934
- [boy 2] Let’s play basketball.
- [exclaims] Oh, oh!

435
00:23:15,310 --> 00:23:16,144
[boy 3] Hey!

436
00:23:17,938 --> 00:23:19,606
Ibyang, stay here, okay?

437
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:21,691
Yo Karla, mah men!

438
00:23:21,775 --> 00:23:24,069
- [shrieks]
- [Karla]

439
00:23:24,152 --> 00:23:25,862
[exclaims] Shoo!

440
00:23:25,946 --> 00:23:29,032
Oh, who’s that little kid?

441
00:23:29,116 --> 00:23:30,575
Just don’t make trouble.

442
00:23:31,993 --> 00:23:34,704
My name isn’t "basta".

443
00:23:34,788 --> 00:23:36,414
It’s Ibyang!

444
00:23:36,498 --> 00:23:37,457
Ibyang.

445
00:23:38,625 --> 00:23:40,418
All right, stay here, okay?

446
00:23:40,502 --> 00:23:41,419
We’ll play first.

447
00:23:42,087 --> 00:23:43,672
Can I join, Sister?

448
00:23:45,924 --> 00:23:47,425
You? Play? Are you sure?

449
00:23:48,718 --> 00:23:49,594
Just kidding!

450
00:23:49,678 --> 00:23:52,556
What do I know about basketball anyway?

451
00:23:53,765 --> 00:23:55,892
- [Karla] Hmm…
- [Ibyang] Wait, wait!

452
00:23:57,227 --> 00:23:58,311
Can I have some coins?

453
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:00,188
I’ll buy snacks.

454
00:24:00,772 --> 00:24:02,732
I’m hungry!

455
00:24:02,816 --> 00:24:04,651
We don’t have money,
and you’re asking for more.

456
00:24:04,734 --> 00:24:06,903
Please! Give me, please!

457
00:24:07,404 --> 00:24:08,238
This kid, really.

458
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:11,074
Come back, okay?

459
00:24:12,409 --> 00:24:15,370
Oh. All right, I’ll play now.

460
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:21,293
[funky music playing]

461
00:24:21,376 --> 00:24:22,460
[Karla] Hey, kid!

462
00:24:22,544 --> 00:24:24,880
- [Karla chuckles, mumbles]
- [boy 2 mutters]

463
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:29,926
[boy 1] Wow!

464
00:24:30,802 --> 00:24:32,304
[funky music continues]

465
00:24:32,387 --> 00:24:33,513
Yes, sir.

466
00:24:33,597 --> 00:24:35,807
I’m just finishing one job.

467
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:39,477
It’s a bit of a personal mission.

468
00:24:39,561 --> 00:24:42,105
Then I’ll take care
of your missing rooster.

469
00:24:46,234 --> 00:24:47,235
Okay, sir.

470
00:24:48,820 --> 00:24:49,654
- Godmother.
- But…

471
00:24:51,656 --> 00:24:54,868
I need a disguise
to get inside Endless Nights.

472
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:57,120
Then contact Lee.

473
00:24:57,204 --> 00:25:00,207
Isn’t he the one you go to
when you need to change your look?

474
00:25:00,290 --> 00:25:01,374
[clicks tongue] That’s the problem.

475
00:25:02,042 --> 00:25:03,668
He’s no longer in the Philippines.

476
00:25:03,752 --> 00:25:06,254
[clicks tongue] Who else could help me?

477
00:25:06,838 --> 00:25:10,800
Tonet has talent in makeup.

478
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:12,177
Maybe she can help you.

479
00:25:13,386 --> 00:25:14,763
- [Cita mutters]
- That’s true.

480
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:18,725
That kind of skill could work.

481
00:25:18,808 --> 00:25:20,101
[upbeat music playing]

482
00:25:20,185 --> 00:25:21,353
Do you think that's okay?

483
00:25:22,062 --> 00:25:24,648
How? You fired her, remember?

484
00:25:24,731 --> 00:25:26,191
[Atoy clicks tongue, chuckles]

485
00:25:26,691 --> 00:25:30,820
[intense music playing]

486
00:25:37,035 --> 00:25:40,121
[Ibyang] As they say,
no big thing can get into the eye.

487
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:41,831
[Ibyang] <i>Don’t worry, Sister Ame.</i>

488
00:25:41,915 --> 00:25:43,083
<i>I’m coming!</i>

489
00:25:43,166 --> 00:25:45,961
- [in English] How about a rematch?
- Yes. [in English] Winner takes all.

490
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:47,170
I’ll shoot for three points.

491
00:25:47,254 --> 00:25:48,421
[boy 1] <i>Three pointers are too easy.</i>

492
00:25:48,505 --> 00:25:49,381
[in English] <i>Halfcourt shot.</i>

493
00:25:49,464 --> 00:25:51,174
You have to win always

494
00:25:51,258 --> 00:25:53,385
because that’s the only way
to get out of here.

495
00:25:53,468 --> 00:25:56,429
[Darryl] <i>Even that man you said you saw?</i>

496
00:25:56,513 --> 00:25:58,723
<i>With all the guards here?</i>

497
00:25:58,807 --> 00:25:59,641
<i>He’s useless!</i>

498
00:25:59,724 --> 00:26:00,809
NEXT

499
00:26:00,892 --> 00:26:02,102
- [muffled screaming]
- Shh!

500
00:26:02,185 --> 00:26:04,896
- Why is there a child here?
- I know her.

501
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:06,523
You know this kid?

502
00:26:06,606 --> 00:26:08,441
[intense music continues]
